                android:text="1. Prepare the Chicken:

Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).

Season the chicken breasts with salt and black pepper on both sides.

2. Set Up a Breading Station:

Place the flour in a shallow dish.

In another dish, beat the eggs.

In a third dish, combine breadcrumbs and grated Parmesan cheese.

3. Bread the Chicken:

Dredge each chicken breast in the flour, shaking off any excess.

Dip the floured chicken into the beaten eggs, ensuring it is fully coated.

Coat the chicken with the breadcrumb-Parmesan mixture, pressing the breadcrumbs onto the surface to adhere.

4. Fry the Chicken:

Heat enough vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat to cover the bottom.

Once the oil is hot, add the breaded chicken breasts and cook for 3-4 minutes per side or until golden brown and cooked through.

Place the cooked chicken on a paper towel-lined plate to absorb excess oil.

5. Assemble the Parmesan Chicken:

In a baking dish, spread a thin layer of marinara sauce.

Place the fried chicken breasts in the baking dish.

Spoon more marinara sauce over the top of each chicken breast.

Sprinkle shredded mozzarella and grated Parmesan cheese over each chicken breast.

6. Bake:

Bake in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.
7. Garnish and Serve:

Garnish with fresh basil or parsley if desired.

Serve the Parmesan chicken over pasta or with a side of your favorite vegetables."
